</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
This genus is very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Laccophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laccophilus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laccophilus</taxonomicName>
Leach, 1815, with the major difference being presence of apically acute metatibial spurs in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Laccoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laccoporus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laccoporus</taxonomicName>
(apically bifid in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Laccophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laccophilus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laccophilus</taxonomicName>
). However, this character has been shown to be reversible in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Laccophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laccophilus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laccophilus</taxonomicName>
, even though rarely so (
<bibRefCitation author="Balke, M" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Zoology" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="295 - 320" title="A review of the New Guinea species of Laccophilus with notes on regional melanism (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." volume="10" year="1997">Balke et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
). We suspect that a study of DNA sequence data will reveal 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Laccoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laccoporus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laccoporus</taxonomicName>
in a position within 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Laccophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laccophilus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laccophilus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
